.container.application-container
  .row
    .col-sm-12
      - if @application.errors.any?
        #error_explanation.alert.alert-danger
          %h2= "Oops looks like you have #{pluralize(@application.errors.count, "error")}, which stopped this application from being submitted."
          %ul
            - @application.errors.full_messages.each do |msg|
              %li= msg
      %h1 New application
      %h3 Judging Criteria
      %p Initial grants usually average 500-1000 dollars each. These grants are judged on the following criteria:
      %ul
        %li Projects must have an innovative factor: technological/process.
        %li Projects must have a technological component.
        %li Projects should have a good management team which is dedicated to implementation.
        %li Projects must be feasible.
        %li Projects must be in accordance with the Weiss Tech House ideals and mission.
        %li The innovative part of the project must be completed by the team and not outsourced.
      %p After the initial grant, teams can pitch once again for additional funding. These subsequent pitches are judged on the following criteria.
      %ul
        %li How has your team used the initial grant?
        %li What milestones has your team been able to reach with the initial grant?
        %li How does your team plan to use the additional funding?
        %li What milestones does your team plan to reach with the additional funding?
        %li What Tech House resources besides funding have your team utilized?
        %li Did your team stay in contact with your project manager and give him any project updates?
      %h3 Use of funds conditions:
      %p All proposed uses for the Innovation Fund grant must be initially approved by the teamâ€™s project manager and then ultimately by the entire Innovation Fund Committee. Common uses for Innovation Fund grants include:
      %ul
        %li Raw materials used to construct a prototype
        %li Server costs
        %li Necessary packaged software, but not the payment for a professional to write computer code
        %li Security certificates
